    "root_cause": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "<div class='page-width'><h2>The Connection <strong>You’ve Been Missing</strong></h2><h3>Your <strong>Hidden</strong> Drainage System</h3><p>Your lymphatic system is your body’s internal cleaning crew—a network of vessels that processes <strong>3–4 liters of cellular waste and excess fluid every single day.</strong> When it’s working properly, you don’t even know it exists.</p><p><strong>But after age 35, declining estrogen hijacks this system’s ability to function.</strong> Vessel pumping weakens, one-way valves fail, protein clogs form, and vessel walls become leaky. Instead of processing and removing waste, it backs up in your tissues.</p><p>That’s why you’re bloated. That’s why your ankles swell. That’s why you see cellulite. That’s why you feel exhausted and foggy. <strong>Your cells are literally sitting in their own waste—and your body can’t flush it out.</strong></p></div>",
        "color_scheme": "",
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 52
      }
    },
